-29,-8,-42,-41,-52,-27,-57,-16,-9,10,5,29]} 1. e4 e6 2. d3 d5 3. Qe2 Nf6 4. Nf3
Be7 5. g3 b6 6. Bg2 Bb7 7. e5 Nfd7 8. h4 c5 9. O-O Nc6 10. c4 d4 11. Na3 h6 12.
h5 a6 13. Nc2 Qc7 14. Re1 O-O-O 15. a3 g6 16. hxg6 fxg6 {[#]} 17. Rb1 g5 18.
Bh3 Nf8 ({Black is missing a great reinforcement of his long diagonal pressure:
} 18... Rdf8 $3 {Creates the unstoppable threat of an exchange sacrifice in
the line:} 19. Bxe6 Rxf3 20. Qxf3 Ncxe5 21. Qe2 (21. Qf5 Rf8) 21... Nf3+ $19)
19. b4 Kb8 20. b5 axb5 21. cxb5 Na5 22. Bd2 c4 ({One more missed opportunity:} 
22... Nc4 $1 $17 {would have won a very important pawn.}) 23. Bxa5 bxa5 24.
Ncxd4 $18 cxd3 25. Nc6+ Ka8 26. Qe3 Rd5 27. Qa7# 1-0

[Event "Buenos Aires"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "1970.??.??"]
[Round "8"]
[White "Fischer, Robert James"]
[Black "Panno, Oscar"]
[Result "1-0"]
[ECO "A04"]
[Annotator "Garry Kasparov"]
[PlyCount "71"]
[EventDate "1970.??.??"]
[SourceTitle "My Great Predecessors 4"]
[Source "Everyman Chess"]
[SourceDate "2009.12.12"]
[SourceVersion "1"]
