{I will not hide the fact that the Hedgehog is one of my favourite openings
with black. But since I open the game with 1.Nf3 quite frequently, it also is
a cross-point of my repertoire. Since I have earlier made the repertoire
database for Modern Chess with this opening from Black's point of view, I will
now show some typical ideas for White. We will divide the material into the
following categories: 1) White plays b2-b3 and Bb2 with two sub-categories 1a)
White exchanges the light-squared bishops 1b) White plays e2-e4 without
exchanging the light-squared bishops. 2) White plays Be3. This database is
intended as a guide for the way White should relate to this opening. There is
no clear refutation of it, but one has to be alert to using the favourable
situations that may occur during the middlegame.}  *

