{[%evp 0,105,16,-12,11,14,16,-33,-30,-15,-17,7,11,10,9,5,12,13,5,10,15,19,18,
-4,7,0,9,-49,-5,-17,-5,-16,25,-4,29,38,39,32,38,41,54,45,55,57,50,53,60,78,113,
99,127,155,150,106,107,55,117,99,113,43,77,99,88,97,76,100,100,61,66,88,88,95,
89,109,107,107,123,60,134,127,118,118,118,163,147,137,162,157,201,201,186,186,
186,216,213,205,230,230,222,192,232,177,195,228,293,313,313,329] Even though
the opening was different in this game, the position in the critical moment is
typical for the English Hedgehog already. Black made the same mistake as in
the previous game.} 1. c4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e6 6. a3
Bc5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. e4 O-O 9. Be2 b6 10. O-O Bb7 11. Bf4 d6 12. Rc1 Rc8 13. Re1
Ne5 14. Nd2 Nfd7 15. Be3 Qc7 16. b4 Qb8 17. f4 Ng6 18. g3 Rfe8 19. Bf3 Qa8 20.
Bf2 Ngf8 21. Qe2 Qb8 22. Red1 {We can notice that the knights are slightly
unusually placed on f8 and d2. White does not seem to have any threats,
inducing Black to play carelessly.} g6 $2 {With the knight on f8, this looks
like a strange move even if there was no clear refutation of it.} (22... a6 $5
23. e5 dxe5 24. fxe5 Bxf3 (24... Ng6 25. Bxb7 Qxb7 26. Nf3 Red8 $5) 25. Nxf3
Red8 {followed by ...Ng6.}) (22... h6 $5) 23. e5 $1 {Judit confessed that she
did not see this move coming. Tis probably happened because she did not have a
knight on f6.} Bc6 24. Bd4 Red8 25. Bxc6 Rxc6 26. Nf3 dxe5 27. fxe5 $16 {
Black does not have ...Ng6 and the square on f6 is weak. WHite has a clear
advantage already.} Rdc8 28. Ne4 Qc7 29. Nfd2 a6 30. Nf2 Bg5 31. Rf1 Bxd2 32.
Qxd2 Nxe5 33. Bxe5 Qxe5 34. Ng4 Rd6 35. Nh6+ Kg7 36. Rxf7+ Kh8 37. Qf2 Qd4 38.
c5 bxc5 39. Qxd4+ Rxd4 40. Rxc5 Rcd8 41. Rcc7 Rd1+ 42. Kg2 R1d2+ 43. Kh3 R2d5
44. Ng4 Rh5+ 45. Kg2 Rd2+ 46. Kf3 Rf5+ 47. Ke3 Rxf7 48. Rxf7 Rd8 49. Nf6 Rb8
50. Kf4 h6 51. Ke5 a5 52. bxa5 Ra8 53. a6 1-0

