{[%evp 0,89,35,16,27,-3,19,21,20,5,14,28,19,31,31,9,26,18,36,38,39,39,39,30,38,
-10,93,137,123,82,71,74,61,87,59,26,23,19,19,-83,-97,-114,-98,-106,-127,-127,
-99,-154,-136,-146,51,45,24,26,44,21,25,56,59,45,41,41,90,102,138,133,152,193,
198,175,175,171,169,192,222,233,225,259,259,252,254,200,211,218,222,248,254,
255,331,348,361,363]} 1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. Nc3 e6 4. g3 b6 5. Bg2 Bb7 6. O-O
Be7 7. Re1 d6 8. e4 a6 9. d4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 Qc7 11. Be3 O-O 12. g4 $5 {A
psychological trap, into which Black will fall.} (12. Rc1 {is the normal move.}
) 12... Qxc4 $2 {Since White has started the attack earlier than usual, Black
thought that this was the right way to punish him.} ({In fact, he should have
taken advantage of the missing rook on c1 with} 12... Nc6 $1 {when Nd5 is not
possible.} 13. Nxc6 Bxc6 14. g5 Nd7 {After exchanging one knight, Black does
not have problems of coordination.}) 13. Rc1 Qc8 14. g5 $6 ({White misses the
most convincing move:} 14. Nd5 $1 Qd8 15. Nxe6 fxe6 16. Bxb6 Qe8 (16... exd5
17. Bxd8 Bxd8 {Vaganian refrained from the sacrifice because of this variation,
yielding Black three minor pieces for the queen. However, WHite can take
advantage of Black's lack in development and weaknesses on light squares with
a few accurate moves.} 18. g5 Nxe4 (18... Nfd7 19. e5 $1 $18 {may be easy to
miss.}) 19. Qb3 Rf7 20. Rxe4 (20. Bh3 $18) 20... dxe4 21. Rc7 $5 Bxc7 22. Qxb7
$18) 17. Nxe7+ Qxe7 18. Rc7 Qe8 19. Rxb7 Qc6 {This line also features some
interesting moments.} 20. e5 (20. Ra7 {only looks simpler. It also requires
some accurate calculation.} Qxb6 21. Rxa8 Nxg4 22. Re2 Nxf2 23. Rxb8 $1 $18)
20... Nd5 (20... d5 21. exf6 Qxb7 22. Rxe6 $18 {This would follow after other
moves, too.}) 21. Bxd5 exd5 22. Re7 Qxb6 23. Qxd5+ Kh8 24. Qf7 $1 Rg8 25. Re8
$1 Nc6 $5 26. Qxg8#) 14... Ne8 15. Nd5 Qd8 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7 {Even so, WHite has
excellent compensation for the pawn, but the game goes on.} 17. a4 g6 18. Qb3
e5 19. Qxb6 exd4 20. Bxd4 a5 21. Re3 Ra6 22. Qb5 Nc6 23. Bf6 Nxf6 24. gxf6 Qxf6
25. Qxb7 Nb4 26. Rc7 Qd4 27. Bf1 Raa8 28. Rxf7 Rxf7 29. Qxa8+ Kg7 30. Qxa5 d5
31. Qb5 Qf6 32. Qe2 Nc6 33. Bg2 Nd4 34. Qd2 dxe4 35. Rxe4 Rd7 36. Qc3 h5 37. a5
Kh7 38. h3 h4 39. Kh1 Qxf2 40. Qe1 Qxe1+ 41. Rxe1 Nb3 42. a6 Ra7 43. Re3 Nc5
44. b4 Nxa6 45. Ra3 1-0

