114,144,145,123,121,113,133,143,139,155,143,136,139,139,139,139,141,129,150,
183,236,303,314,315,323,323,324,324,333] In this game, we will examine White's
most precise move order with 15.Rfc1. Additionally, we will take a look at the
pawn structures arising after the advance ...b5-b4. The first 15 moves repeat
