Qxc4 b5 7. Qc2 Bb7 8. Nc3 a6 9. a4 Nbd7 10. O-O Qb6 11. d3 c5 12. e4 Be7 13. h3
O-O 14. Be3 Rac8 15. Rfc1 {Before proceeding with axb5 followed by b2-b4,
White puts his rook on an optimal square, thus overprotecting the c3-knight.}
Rfd8 {The most natural continuation.} ({In general, Black usually tries to
refrain from} 15... b4 {because after} 16. Nb1 {[%cal Gb1d2,Gd2c4,Gf3d2,Gd2b3]
the white knight is heading to the c4-square. Ideally, White is planning to
