{[#]} 10. Ne5 $1 {This is a very important prophylactic move designed to
prevent ...Nc6. Now, Black cannot develop his queenside.} Qc7 {As we know, the
queen is pretty vulnerable on c7. White always has Bf4 at his disposal.} 11.
Nc4 Nc6 12. Nc3 Nd4 ({Black can never play} 12... b6 $2 {because of} 13. Bf4 {
[%csl Ra8][%cal Gc4e5,Gg2a8] with Ne5 to follow.}) 13. Qd1 e5 {At this point,
the most energetic would have been} 14. f4 ({In the game, White decided to
make use of the weak d5-square with} 14. Bg5 $14 {which is a decent option as
well.}) 14... exf4 15. Bxf4 {White's superior piece activity provides him with
an initiative.} 1-0

