{[%evp 0,34,24,12,12,-7,9,10,10,12,36,18,33,19,49,10,25,36,23,23,39,39,38,34,
44,46,31,29,9,0,7,-8,0,0,1,-8,-3]} 1. Nf3 d5 2. g3 c6 3. Bg2 Bf5 4. O-O e6 5.
d3 h6 6. c4 $6 {If White wants to play the setup with c4, it was better to
play this move before d3 or to wait for Nbd7.} dxc4 $1 7. dxc4 Qxd1 {In my
opinion this endgame is completely harmless for Black.} 8. Rxd1 Nf6 9. Nc3 Bc2
{It resembles a lot the position from the London system with g6, but with
reversed colors. I quite like Black's position and believe that Black has
decent chances to play for a win.} 10. Rd2 Bh7 11. Rd1 Bb4 12. Bd2 O-O 13. Ne5
Rd8 14. a3 Be7 15. Bf4 Nbd7 16. Nxd7 Rxd7 17. Rxd7 Nxd7 $11 {The game is equal,
but Jobava manages to outplay his lower-rated opponent.} 0-1

