{[%evp 100,126,85,66,66,0,66,44,225,266,290,287,301,310,310,320,584,668,717,
934,944,982,982,1076,1204,1230,1064,1298,1280] I am showing you this example
to show you a typical mistake which White can make in this line} 1. Nf3 d5 2.
g3 c6 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. d3 Bg4 5. Nbd2 e6 6. O-O Be7 7. e4 O-O 8. e5 $4 {When a
Black knight is still on "b8" this move is a blunder. Now Black gets a perfect
version of the French defense. The "f6" knight has a good square on "d7," and
the "b8" is coming to c6 after the c6-c5 break.} Nfd7 $15 9. d4 c5 10. c3 Nc6
11. h3 Bh5 12. g4 Bg6 13. Re1 $2 {It is hard to suggest anything better for
White, but this move loses on the spot.} cxd4 14. cxd4 Nb4 $17 15. Nf1 Nc2 16.
Bf4 Nxa1 {The game length for 30 more moves, but White could resign here.} 0-1

